Durban - The ANC's provincial conference has descended into chaos as delegates heckled and booed some national leaders on Friday night.

ANC national chairperson, Gwede Mantashe, who was due to deliver a keynote address had a tough time trying to control the delegates who broke into song whenever he tried to speak.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
The coordinator of the ANC provincial task team Sihle Zikalala pleaded for calm. 















